name: Butterfree V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned.

name: Butterfree VMAX
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned.

name: Paras
flavorText: The mushrooms, known as tochukaso, are controlling the bug. Even if the bug bugs the mushrooms, they tell it to bug off.

name: Parasect
flavorText: The bug is mostly dead, with the mushroom on its back having become the main body. If the mushroom comes off, the bug stops moving.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Carnivine
flavorText: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.
Attack1Text: You may draw cards until you have 5 cards in your hand.
Attack2Text: Heal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Pansage
flavorText: It's good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It's kind enough to share them with friends.

name: Simisage
flavorText: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Karrablast
flavorText: Its strange physiology reacts to electrical energy in interesting ways. The presence of a Shelmet will cause this Pokémon to evolve.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Shelmet
flavorText: When attacked, it tightly shuts the lid of its shell. This reaction fails to protect it from Karrablast, however, because they can still get into the shell.

name: Accelgor
flavorText: It moves with blinding speed and lobs poison at foes. Featuring Accelgor as a main character is a surefire way to make a movie or comic popular.

name: Rowlet
flavorText: At a distance, it launches its sharp feathers while flying about. If the enemy gets too close, Rowlet switches tactics and delivers vicious kicks.
Ability1Text: If you played Bird Keeper from your hand during this turn, ignore all Energy in this Pokémon's attack costs.
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Dartrix
flavorText: It throws one knifelike feather after another at its enemies, and each one precisely strikes a weak point. These feathers are known as blade quills.

name: Decidueye
flavorText: As if wielding a bow, it launches the arrow quills hidden among the feathers of its wings. Decidueye's shots never miss.
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon V and Pokémon-GX.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Bounsweet
flavorText: Its body gives off a sweet, fruity scent that is extremely appetizing to bird Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Grass Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Steenee
flavorText: As it twirls like a dancer, a sweet smell spreads out around it. Anyone who inhales the scent will feel a surge of happiness.
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon.

name: Tsareena
flavorText: This feared Pokémon has long, slender legs and a cruel heart. It shows no mercy as it stomps on its opponents.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon for each Energy attached to this Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: You may put an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon into their hand.

name: Wimpod
flavorText: It's nature's cleaner—it eats anything and everything, including garbage and rotten things. The ground near its nest is always clean.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Golisopod
flavorText: It will do anything to win, taking advantage of every opening and finishing opponents off with the small claws on its front legs.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 more damage for each of your opponent's Pokémon V and Pokémon-GX in play.
Attack2Text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Charizard V
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Charizard VMAX
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Houndoom V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.
Attack2Text: If your Benched Fire Pokémon have any damage counters on them, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Torchic
flavorText: A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Combusken
flavorText: During a battle, the hot flame in its body increases. Its kicks have outstanding destructive power.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Blaziken
flavorText: When facing a tough foe, it looses flames from its wrists. Its powerful legs let it jump clear over buildings.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is in play, it is Fire and Fighting type.
Attack1Text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Heatran
flavorText: Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

name: Pansear
flavorText: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Simisear
flavorText: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Galarian Darmanitan
flavorText: Anger has reignited its atrophied flame sac. This Pokémon spews fire everywhere as it rampages indiscriminately.
Attack2Text: You may discard all Water Energy from this Pokémon. If you do, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Larvesta
flavorText: It protects itself with flame. Long years ago, people believed Larvesta had a nest on the sun.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Volcarona
flavorText: According to legends, it was hatched from a flaming cocoon to save people and Pokémon that were suffering from the cold.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has no damage counters on it before this attack does damage, this attack does nothing.

name: Fletchinder
flavorText: Its speed right after takeoff already puts it in the top speed class of all bird Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Talonflame
flavorText: Bird Pokémon make up most of its diet. It approaches at high speeds and smacks them down to the ground with its powerful kick.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokémon (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokémon is now Burned.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

name: Centiskorch V
Attack1Text: You may discard an Energy from this Pokémon. If you do, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Centiskorch VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon. If you did any damage with this attack, you may attach a Fire Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

name: Galarian Mr. Mime
flavorText: Its talent is tap-dancing. It can also manipulate temperatures to create a floor of ice, which this Pokémon can kick up to use as a barrier.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Galarian Mr. Rime
flavorText: It's highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may switch 1 of your opponent's face-down Prize cards with the top card of their deck. (The cards stay face down.)
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile that has the Mad Party attack.

name: Suicune
flavorText: Said to be the embodiment of north winds, it can instantly purify filthy, murky water.
Attack2Text: Put 2 Water Energy attached to this Pokémon into your hand.

name: Feebas
flavorText: Although unattractive and unpopular, this Pokémon's marvelous vitality has made it a subject of research.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Milotic
flavorText: Milotic has provided inspiration to many artists. It has even been referred to as the most beautiful Pokémon of all.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may heal 20 damage from each of your Pokémon.

name: Relicanth
flavorText: The reason it hasn't changed at all in a hundred million years is that it's apparently already a perfect life-form.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Rare Fossil cards and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Panpour
flavorText: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

name: Simipour
flavorText: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Galarian Darumaka
flavorText: It lived in snowy areas for so long that its fire sac cooled off and atrophied. It now has an organ that generates cold instead.

name: Galarian Darmanitan
flavorText: On days when blizzards blow through, it comes down to where people live. It stashes food in the snowball on its head, taking it home for later.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Crushing Headbutt.

name: Vanillite
flavorText: Unable to survive in hot areas, it makes itself comfortable by breathing out air cold enough to cause snow. It burrows into the snow to sleep.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Vanillish
flavorText: By drinking pure water, it grows its icy body. This Pokémon can be hard to find on days with warm, sunny weather.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Vanilluxe
flavorText: When its anger reaches a breaking point, this Pokémon unleashes a fierce blizzard that freezes every creature around it, be they friend or foe.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Cubchoo
flavorText: When this Pokémon is in good health, its snot becomes thicker and stickier. It will smear its snot on anyone it doesn't like.

name: Beartic
flavorText: It swims through frigid seas, searching for prey. From its frozen breath, it forms icy fangs that are harder than steel.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 50 damage to itself.

name: Wishiwashi
flavorText: Individually, they're incredibly weak. It's by gathering up into schools that they're able to confront opponents.
Attack1Text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw 8 cards.

name: Mareanie
flavorText: The first symptom of its sting is numbness. The next is an itching sensation so intense that it's impossible to resist the urge to claw at your skin.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Toxapex
flavorText: To survive in the cold waters of Galar, this Pokémon forms a dome with its legs, enclosing its body so it can capture its own body heat.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon and heal all damage from it.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Dracovish
flavorText: Powerful legs and jaws made it the apex predator of its time. Its own overhunting of its prey was what drove it to extinction.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your opponent can't play any Pokémon from their hand to evolve their Pokémon.

name: Arctovish
flavorText: Though it's able to capture prey by freezing its surroundings, it has trouble eating the prey afterward because its mouth is on top of its head.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 60 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Mareep
flavorText: Rubbing its fleece generates electricity. You'll want to pet it because it's cute, but if you use your bare hand, you'll get a painful shock.

name: Flaaffy
flavorText: It stores electricity in its fluffy fleece. If it stores up too much, it will start to go bald in those patches.

name: Ampharos
flavorText: Its tail shines bright and strong. It has been prized since long ago as a beacon for sailors.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Electrike
flavorText: It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.
Attack1Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Manectric
flavorText: It stimulates its own muscles with electricity, so it can move quickly. It eases its soreness with electricity, too, so it can recover quickly as well.
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Vikavolt V
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, they can't play any Item cards from their hand.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Tapu Koko
flavorText: The lightning-wielding guardian deity of Melemele, Tapu Koko is brimming with curiosity and appears before people from time to time.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.

name: Toxel
flavorText: It stores poison in an internal poison sac and secretes that poison through its skin. If you touch this Pokémon, a tingling sensation follows.

name: Toxtricity
flavorText: Capable of generating 15,000 volts of electricity, this Pokémon looks down on all that would challenge it.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard the top 5 cards of your opponent's deck. If tails, discard the top 5 cards of your deck.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Pincurchin
flavorText: It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it off rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of its spines.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Dracozolt
flavorText: In ancient times, it was unbeatable thanks to its powerful lower body, but it went extinct anyway after it depleted all its plant-based food sources.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Amping Up attack does 90 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Arctozolt
flavorText: The shaking of its freezing upper half is what generates its electricity. It has a hard time walking around.
Ability1Text: Whenever your opponent attaches an Energy card from their hand to 1 of their Pokémon, put 2 damage counters on that Pokémon.

name: Jigglypuff
flavorText: The songs they sing are totally different depending on the region they live in. Some even sound like they're shouting!

name: Wigglytuff
flavorText: When it gets angry, it inhales with all its might, and its body gradually inflates. Sometimes they can grow 20 times larger!
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 90 damage for each heads.

name: Mew V
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage for each Energy attached to both Active Pokémon.

name: Snubbull
flavorText: In contrast to its appearance, it's quite timid. When playing with other puppy Pokémon, it sometimes gets bullied.

name: Granbull
flavorText: Although it's popular with young people, Granbull is timid and sensitive, so it's totally incompetent as a watchdog.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

name: Lunatone
flavorText: The phase of the moon apparently has some effect on its power. It's active on the night of a full moon.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 4 cards of either player's deck and put them back in any order.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Gothita
flavorText: Though they're still only babies, there's psychic power stored in their ribbonlike feelers, and sometimes they use that power to fight.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 5 cards of your opponent's deck and put them back in any order.

name: Gothorita
flavorText: It's said that when stars shine in the night sky, this Pokémon will spirit away sleeping children. Some call it the Witch of Punishment.
Attack1Text: Choose a random card from your opponent's hand. Your opponent reveals that card and shuffles it into their deck.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

name: Gothitelle
flavorText: It has tremendous psychic power, but it dislikes conflict. It's also able to predict the future based on the movement of the stars.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: Choose 2 random cards from your opponent's hand. Your opponent reveals those cards and shuffles them into their deck.

name: Golett
flavorText: They were sculpted from clay in ancient times. No one knows why, but some of them are driven to continually line up boulders.

name: Golurk
flavorText: Artillery platforms built into the walls of ancient castles served as perches from which Golurk could fire energy beams.

name: Dedenne
flavorText: Its upper whiskers are sensors that survey its surroundings. Its lower whiskers are organs that shoot electricity.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile that has the Mad Party attack.

name: Morelull
flavorText: Pokémon living in the forest eat the delicious caps on Morelull's head. The caps regrow overnight.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Shiinotic
flavorText: Its flickering spores lure in prey and put them to sleep. Once this Pokémon has its prey snoozing, it drains their vitality with its fingertips.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't attack.
Attack2Text: If Glimwood Tangle is in play, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Mimikyu
flavorText: It wears a rag fashioned into a Pikachu costume in an effort to look less scary. Unfortunately, the costume only makes it creepier.
Ability1Text: Your opponent's Benched Pokémon can't be healed.

name: Sinistea
flavorText: This Pokémon is said to have been born when a lonely spirit possessed a cold, leftover cup of tea.
Attack1Text: Put 2 damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Polteageist
flavorText: This species lives in antique teapots. Most pots are forgeries, but on rare occasions, an authentic work is found.
Ability1Text: You must discard a Pokémon that has the Mad Party attack from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw 2 cards.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile that has the Mad Party attack.

name: Diglett
flavorText: If a Diglett digs through a field, it leaves the soil perfectly tilled and ideal for planting crops.

name: Dugtrio
flavorText: A team of Diglett triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Larvitar
flavorText: Born deep underground, it comes aboveground and becomes a pupa once it has finished eating the surrounding soil.

name: Pupitar
flavorText: Even sealed in its shell, it can move freely. Hard and fast, it has outstanding destructive power.
Attack2Text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokémon and put it onto this Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Tyranitar
flavorText: Its body can't be harmed by any sort of attack, so it is very eager to make challenges against enemies.
Attack1Text: Discard a Stadium in play.
Attack2Text: Discard the top 5 cards of your deck.

name: Trapinch
flavorText: Its nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit in the desert. Once something has fallen in, there is no escape.
Attack1Text: If a Stadium is in play, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Vibrava
flavorText: The ultrasonic waves it generates by rubbing its two wings together cause severe headaches.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Flygon
flavorText: This Pokémon hides in the heart of sandstorms it creates and seldom appears where people can see it.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your opponent's Active Pokémon can't retreat.
Attack1Text: If your opponent has a Stadium in play, discard it. If you discarded a Stadium in this way, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Solrock
flavorText: When it rotates itself, it gives off light similar to the sun, thus blinding its foes.
Ability1Text: If you have Lunatone in play, your opponent's Pokémon in play have no Resistance.

name: Hippopotas
flavorText: It moves through the sands with its mouth open, swallowing sand along with its prey. It gets rid of the sand by spouting it from its nose.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

name: Hippowdon
flavorText: Stones can get stuck in the ports on their bodies. Dwebble help dislodge such stones, so Hippowdon look after these Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 80 damage for each heads.

name: Rhyperior V
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Heavy Rock Artillery.

name: Diggersby
flavorText: With power equal to an excavator, it can dig through dense bedrock. It's a huge help during tunnel construction.

name: Passimian
flavorText: Displaying amazing teamwork, they follow the orders of their boss as they all help out in the search for their favorite berries.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Galarian Sirfetch'd
flavorText: Only Farfetch'd that have survived many battles can attain this evolution. When this Pokémon's leek withers, it will retire from combat.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon can't use Meteor Assault again until it leaves the Active Spot.

name: Galarian Slowbro V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may make your opponent's Active Pokémon Poisoned.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

name: Grimer
flavorText: The wastewater coming from factories is clean these days, so Grimer have nothing to eat. They're said to be on the verge of extinction.
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

name: Muk
flavorText: Because they scatter germs everywhere, they've long been targeted for extermination, leading to a steep decline in their population.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. During Pokémon Checkup, put 3 damage counters on that Pokémon instead of 1.

name: Spinarak
flavorText: Although the poison from its fangs isn't that strong, it's potent enough to weaken prey that gets caught in its web.

name: Ariados
flavorText: It spews threads from its mouth to catch its prey. When night falls, it leaves its web to go hunt aggressively.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Evolution Pokémon with their Active Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Crobat V
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand. You can't use more than 1 Dark Asset Ability each turn.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Darkrai
flavorText: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon has any Darkness Energy attached, it takes 20 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Darkness Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Purrloin
flavorText: It steals things from people just to amuse itself with their frustration. A rivalry exists between this Pokémon and Nickit.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Liepard
flavorText: Don't be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokémon.
Ability1Text: This Pokémon can't be Paralyzed.

name: Deino
flavorText: When it encounters something, its first urge is usually to bite it. If it likes what it tastes, it will commit the associated scent to memory.

name: Zweilous
flavorText: While hunting for prey, Zweilous wanders its territory, its two heads often bickering over which way to go.

name: Hydreigon
flavorText: There are a slew of stories about villages that were destroyed by Hydreigon. It bites anything that moves.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn, you may attach a Darkness Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon.

name: Hoopa
flavorText: It gathers things it likes and passes them through its loop to teleport them to a secret place.
Attack1Text: If this Pokémon didn't move from the Bench to the Active Spot this turn, this attack does nothing. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness.

name: Nickit
flavorText: Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokémon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't attack.

name: Thievul
flavorText: It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Grimmsnarl V
Attack2Text: Put 2 Darkness Energy attached to this Pokémon into your hand.

name: Grimmsnarl VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 more damage for each extra Darkness Energy attached to this Pokémon (in addition to this attack's cost). You can't add more than 100 damage in this way.

name: Eternatus V
Attack1Text: You may attach a Darkness Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon VMAX, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Eternatus VMAX
Ability1Text: If all of your Pokémon in play are Darkness type, you can have up to 8 Pokémon on your Bench, and you can't put non-Darkness Pokémon into play. (If this Ability stops working, discard Pokémon from your Bench until you have 5.)
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage for each of your Darkness Pokémon in play.

name: Scizor V
Attack1Text: Discard a Pokémon Tool and a Special Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Scizor VMAX
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Skarmory
flavorText: Its body is draped in steel armor. It looks heavy, but it can fly at speeds of up to 185 miles an hour!
Attack1Text: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool attached, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Aron
flavorText: When it evolves, it sheds the steel carapace that covered its whole body and develops a new one.

name: Lairon
flavorText: It habitually shows off its strength with the sparks it creates by ramming its steel body into boulders.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Aggron
flavorText: While seeking iron for food, it digs tunnels by breaking through bedrock with its steel horns.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon has full HP and would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, it is not Knocked Out, and its remaining HP becomes 10.

name: Escavalier
flavorText: They use shells they've stolen from Shelmet to arm and protect themselves. They're very popular Pokémon in the Galar region.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. If 1 of them is heads, this attack does 20 more damage. If 2 of them are heads, this attack does 70 more damage. If all of them are heads, this attack does 140 more damage.

name: Klink
flavorText: The two minigears that compose this Pokémon are closer than twins. They mesh well only with each other.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Metal Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Klang
flavorText: When Klang goes all out, the minigear links up perfectly with the outer part of the big gear, and this Pokémon's rotation speed increases sharply.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Metal Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Klinklang
flavorText: From its spikes, it launches powerful blasts of electricity. Its red core contains an enormous amount of energy.
Attack2Text: If you don't have Klink and Klang on your Bench, this attack does nothing.

name: Galarian Stunfisk V
Ability1Text: This Pokémon gets +20 HP for each Metal Energy attached to it.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack (even if it is Knocked Out), put 12 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.

name: Meltan
flavorText: It dissolves and eats metal. Circulating liquid metal within its body is how it generates energy.

name: Melmetal
flavorText: At the end of its life-span, Melmetal will rust and fall apart. The small shards left behind will eventually be reborn as Meltan.
Attack1Text: Attach an Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

name: Cufant
flavorText: It digs up the ground with its trunk. It's also very strong, being able to carry loads of over five tons without any problem at all.

name: Copperajah
flavorText: They came over from another region long ago and worked together with humans. Their green skin is resistant to water.
Ability1Text: This Pokémon can't be affected by any Special Conditions.
Attack1Text: If your Benched Pokémon have any damage counters on them, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Kangaskhan
flavorText: You shouldn't get close to the child when it's playing outside its mother's pouch. Its mother is always nearby watching over it.
Attack1Text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon during their last turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Tauros
flavorText: They live in groups. The one with the longest, thickest, and most-scarred horns is the boss of the herd.

name: Sentret
flavorText: It stands on its tail so it can see a long way. If it spots an enemy, it cries loudly to warn its kind.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Furret
flavorText: It makes a nest to suit its long and skinny body. The nest is impossible for other Pokémon to enter.
Attack1Text: Draw 3 cards.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Dunsparce
flavorText: When it sees a person, it digs a hole with its tail to make its escape. If you happen to find one, consider yourself lucky.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, discard the top 2 cards of your opponent's deck.

name: Teddiursa
flavorText: Before food becomes scarce in wintertime, its habit is to hoard food in many hidden locations.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

name: Ursaring
flavorText: Although it has a large body, it is quite skilled at climbing trees. It eats and sleeps in the treetops.
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

name: Lugia
flavorText: It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.
Attack2Text: Put an Energy attached to this Pokémon into your hand.

name: Skitty
flavorText: It shows its cute side by chasing its own tail until it gets dizzy.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for an Energy card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Delcatty
flavorText: It is highly popular among female Trainers for its sublime fur. It does not keep a nest.
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon. The new Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Salamence V
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Salamence VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Max Wings.

name: Starly
flavorText: They flock around mountains and fields, chasing after bug Pokémon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.
Ability1Text: If you played Bird Keeper from your hand during this turn, ignore all Energy in this Pokémon's attack costs.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Staravia
flavorText: It lives in forests and fields. Squabbles over territory occur when flocks collide.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Staraptor
flavorText: When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.
Attack1Text: Move any amount of Energy from your Pokémon to your other Pokémon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Ducklett
flavorText: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.

name: Swanna
flavorText: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.
Ability1Text: If you played Bird Keeper from your hand during this turn, ignore all Energy in this Pokémon's attack costs.
Attack1Text: You may discard a card from your hand. If you do, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Bunnelby
flavorText: It excels at digging holes. Using its ears, it can dig a nest 33 feet deep in one night.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile that has the Mad Party attack.

name: Fletchling
flavorText: Its body is always warm. Trainers who live in cold areas apparently sleep with it in their bed.

name: Skwovet
flavorText: Found throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon becomes uneasy if its cheeks are ever completely empty of berries.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Greedent
flavorText: It stashes berries in its tail—so many berries that they fall out constantly. But this Pokémon is a bit slow-witted, so it doesn't notice the loss.
Attack1Text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tools from your opponent's Active Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Put this Pokémon and all attached cards into your hand.

name: Rookidee
flavorText: It will bravely challenge any opponent, no matter how powerful. This Pokémon benefits from every battle—even a defeat increases its strength a bit.
Attack1Text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tools from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Corvisquire
flavorText: Smart enough to use tools in battle, these Pokémon have been seen picking up rocks and flinging them or using ropes to wrap up enemies.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

name: Corviknight
flavorText: This Pokémon reigns supreme in the skies of the Galar region. The black luster of its steel body could drive terror into the heart of any foe.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may put 1 of your Pokémon, except any Corviknight, and all attached cards into your hand.

name: Butterfree V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned.

name: Houndoom V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.
Attack2Text: If your Benched Fire Pokémon have any damage counters on them, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Centiskorch V
Attack1Text: You may discard an Energy from this Pokémon. If you do, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Vikavolt V
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, they can't play any Item cards from their hand.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Rhyperior V
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Heavy Rock Artillery.

name: Crobat V
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand. You can't use more than 1 Dark Asset Ability each turn.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Scizor V
Attack1Text: Discard a Pokémon Tool and a Special Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Galarian Stunfisk V
Ability1Text: This Pokémon gets +20 HP for each Metal Energy attached to it.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack (even if it is Knocked Out), put 12 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.

name: Salamence V
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Butterfree VMAX
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned.

name: Centiskorch VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon. If you did any damage with this attack, you may attach a Fire Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

name: Eternatus VMAX
Ability1Text: If all of your Pokémon in play are Darkness type, you can have up to 8 Pokémon on your Bench, and you can't put non-Darkness Pokémon into play. (If this Ability stops working, discard Pokémon from your Bench until you have 5.)
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage for each of your Darkness Pokémon in play.

name: Scizor VMAX
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Salamence VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Max Wings.

name: Rillaboom
flavorText: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 2 Grass Energy cards and attach them to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Coalossal
flavorText: It's usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Fire Energy card, a Fighting Energy card, or 1 of each from your discard pile to your Pokémon in any way you like.
